    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="landing-section">
      <div class="landing-section-inner">
        <p class="section-label">Common Questions</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What is Soleur?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Soleur is the company-as-a-service platform. It deploys {{ stats.agents }} AI agents across {{ stats.departments }} business departments &mdash; engineering, marketing, legal, finance, operations, product, sales, and support &mdash; giving a single founder the operational capacity of a full organization. Every problem solved compounds into patterns that accelerate future work.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What is company-as-a-service?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Company-as-a-service means running every business function through a unified platform of AI agents instead of hiring individual employees or contractors for each department. You provide the taste, vision, and decisions &mdash; the agents handle execution across engineering, marketing, legal, sales, and every other department.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">How does Soleur differ from Cursor or GitHub Copilot?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Cursor and Copilot are code editors. Soleur operates across every business department, not only engineering. It includes agents for marketing strategy, legal compliance, financial planning, sales pipeline analysis, and more. It also compounds knowledge over time &mdash; every decision and pattern is captured and reused, making your organization smarter with each project.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Is Soleur free?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Soleur offers two paths. The cloud platform (coming soon) provides managed infrastructure, a web dashboard, and priority support &mdash; pricing starts at the Spark tier. The self-hosted version is open source and free. Both run on Anthropic&rsquo;s Claude models, so your AI costs depend on your Claude usage.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Who is Soleur for?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Solo founders and solopreneurs who refuse to accept that scale requires headcount. Soleur is the only platform that spans every business department and compounds institutional knowledge across projects &mdash; giving one person the operational capacity of a full organization.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">How do I get started?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Join the waitlist for the cloud platform, or install the open-source version and run <code>/soleur:go</code> to start. Describe what you need &mdash; build a feature, validate a business idea, generate legal documents, run a competitive analysis &mdash; and Soleur routes to the right workflow.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

